Race.SummaryText:
PARISHWIDE PROPOSITION
(PUBLIC FACILITIES TAX RENEWAL)

SUMMARY:  10 YEAR, .86 MILLS PROPERTY TAX RENEWAL FOR MAINTAINING AND OPERATING PUBLIC ROAD SYSTEMS, PARKS AND RECREATIONAL FACILITIES, GARBAGE DISPOSAL AND INDUSTRIAL WASTE PROGRAMS, SURFACE WATER DRAINS AND DRAINAGE FACILITIES IN CADDO PARISH, LOUISIANA.
Race.FullText: Shall Caddo Parish, Louisiana (the "Parish"), continue to levy a tax of eighty-six hundredths (.86) mills on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $987,550 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year) for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2009 and ending with the year 2018, for the purpose of maintaining and operating public road systems, parks and recreational facilities, garbage disposal and industrial waste programs, surface water drains and drainage facilities in Caddo Parish, Louisiana?
